<div id="review_947240471" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/947240471" />
    <a title="Czarny Pies" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29160274-czarny-pies"><img alt="Czarny Pies" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1400687408p2/29160274.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/947240471?book_show_action=true">May 24, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Czarny Pies" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Czarny Pies" href="/user/show/29160274-czarny-pies">Czarny Pies</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Anyone who likes dirty jokes</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29160274-czarny-pies?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29160274-czarny-pies?shelf=italian-literature">italian-literature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer947240471" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3541697117336661079">So many people have read this book and so many great authors have borrowed from it, that a GoodReads critic really has no choice but to give it 5 stars.<br/><br/>My favourite day, is the one dedicated to the theme and I quote: &quot;When they are twenty, they need it plenty.&quot; Although, to be honest the book never at any point strays very far from the gutter which explains its perennial appeal.<br/><br/>The problem with the Decameron is that people are terrified by the length. They think of the time required to read all </span>
  <span id="freeText3541697117336661079" style="display:none">So many people have read this book and so many great authors have borrowed from it, that a GoodReads critic really has no choice but to give it 5 stars.<br /><br />My favourite day, is the one dedicated to the theme and I quote: "When they are twenty, they need it plenty." Although, to be honest the book never at any point strays very far from the gutter which explains its perennial appeal.<br /><br />The problem with the Decameron is that people are terrified by the length. They think of the time required to read all 100 stories and back off. I solved the problem by resolving to read ten stories every year and finishing in ten years. Once you do this you can begin without fear of failure.<br /><br />Some people find that it helps to read the book in the Serengetti or at a café beside the Grande Canal of Venice. I read it in the patio in front of my steam bath in the Karelia.<br /><br />I still think that the 10 stories per year plan is the best. It allows you to stay in control of the process. To be honest in the third year, at the steam bath the stories acquired the taste of salty popcorn and I read the last 800 stories in three weeks. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3541697117336661079" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review947240471">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
        <a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link947240471" title="Flag this review as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=947240471&amp;resource_type=Review&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F51799.The_Decameron">flag</a>





